ntsb3723txt-1-5-5-0-3 The airplane landed hard collapsing the left main landing gear then collided with terrain. 
ntsb3723txt-1-5-5-0-7 The rear seat passenger who had a clear view of the 'D ring' which activates the spoilers stated the airplane landed hard then bounced. 
ntsb3723txt-1-5-5-0-10 The airplane was equipped with spoilers installed in the upper side of both wings. 
ntsb3723txt-1-5-5-0-9 Examination of the site by an FAA inspector revealed the airplane came to rest in a ditch off the left side of the runway, approximately 800-1,000 feet from the approach end of the runway. 
